~ scene_1_high
Marcos: Hello, good morning! My name is Marcos and I am from Microsoft’s Security Department. We are calling you because we have received an alert from your IP address indicating that your computer may have a virus.
Marcos: To prevent you from losing some important photos or files, we are here to help you. Do you have your computer nearby?
do update_trust(15)
Personaje: Oh dear… thank goodness you called! A red warning popped up on my computer earlier and I didn’t know what to do. 
Personaje: Are you saying my photos are at risk? Oh please, help me… I have all the photos from my grandson José Antonio’s communion on there…
=> scene_2

~ scene_1_neutral
Marcos: Hello. I am calling urgently from Microsoft Technical Support. Your computer has been infected with a level 4 trojan that is blocking the system.
Marcos: Please, give me access to your computer or your photos and files will be lost in minutes!
set dice_roll = get_neutral_result()
if dice_roll == 1
	do update_trust(15)
	Personaje: Whaaat? In two minutes? Wait, wait… oh my, I’m getting so nervous… what I must do? Please don’t disconnect anything from my computer…
else
	do update_trust(-10)
	Personaje: What? What do you mean in 2 minutes? Listen, I have a lot of respect for IT professionals, but I won’t tolerate being shouted at. I will ask my grandson, he is very good with computers.
=> scene_2

~ scene_1_low
